<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1901-01-04T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1901-01-04T00:00:00-05:00" n="459" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d459">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Hill</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Griscom</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1901-01-04"><hi rend="italic">January 4,
                                1901</hi>.</date></dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 329.]</seg></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have to acknowledge the receipt of your
                            dispatch No. 295, of the 12th ultimo, reporting the courtesies shown by
                            the Sultan to Captain Chester and his staff, of the U. S. S. <hi rend="italic">Kentucky</hi>, during the recent visit of that vessel
                            to Constantinople.</p>
                        <p>You will express to His Majesty, through the proper channel, this
                            Government’s appreciation of the courtesies shown to Captain Chester and
                            his officers.</p>
                        <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">David J. Hill</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Acting Secretary.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                </body></text></TEI>